Quote: Some years ago there was a game among boys [?in Dunedin] called `spangweaselling' - taking kingfishers' nests with the young birds in them and knocking them to bits in the air.
Notes: 1965 Aug 2 WNTV1 `Any Questions' (P. Smithell, Dunedin) [spg SPANGWEASELING]

